explanation: The solution iterates through the characters of word2, comparing them to the corresponding characters in word1. If a mismatch is found, it increments a difference counter. If the counter exceeds 1, it means more than one character needs to be changed, so an empty array is returned. Otherwise, the index of the mismatch is added to the sequence. Finally, the sequence is returned. This approach is efficient as it has a linear time complexity and space complexity.

